 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Director, Enterprise Data Science MD Anderson Cancer Center Houston, TX 77030 Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Summary
 
 
The Director, Enterprise Data Science is accountable for overseeing the Enterprise Data Science team in support of clinical, research, and administrative domains across MD Anderson. The Director is responsible for collaborating across the institution to develop and apply data science approaches. This position is also responsible for developing the architecture, standards and methodologies data scientists will leverage in developing both machine learning and artificial intelligence applications that ensure the best possible outcomes.
 
 
This position ensures that these applications support the mission, goals and operations of the institution and are developed, validated, deployed, and maintained in a timely, accurate, creative and cost-effective manner. The Director will also take a role in raising the institutional awareness of the benefits of data science and help develop educational materials to assure MD Anderson's teams are following best practices on data science approaches.
 
 
The Director will work closely with technology leaders in ideating on the deployment of data science approaches, on designing the technology stack in support of data science, and on the organization of data engineering in support of the best practices for data governance. The Enterprise Data Science team will work on institutional priorities with the freedom to explore novel approaches while also drawing upon the technologies and methods of academic and industry partners.
 
 
 Requirements - Must have the following:
 
 
 Ph.D Degree in Computer/Data Science or other medical related science field
 
 Three years of management experience with a focus on data science
 
 Seven years in data sciences and oncology
 
 Extensive experience working with senior and middle management and clinicians in a team-oriented capacity
 
 Strong familiarity with database tools, development environments, and tuning capabilities
 
 Prefer experience in an academic medical center environment and or industry 
